The paper deals with game-theoretic scenarios and mechanism design, which are typically studied in the sub-category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The focus on social networks and diffusion processes suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of submodular functions and optimization techniques points to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the consideration of stochastic diffusion models and network topologies suggests a possible connection to cs.IT (Information Theory).
